54.6	Brassica	Brassica	Brassica ( br√°s-si-ca) is a genus of plants in the mustard family . The members of the genus are collectively known as cruciferous vegetables, cabbages, or mustards. Crops from this genus are sometimes called cole crops, which is derived from the Latin caulis, meaning stem or cabbage.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Brassica_rapa_plant.jpg/220px-Brassica_rapa_plant.jpg
